HEADWORD: Turpitude
<hw>Tur"pi*tude</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>turpitudo</ets>, from <ets>turpis</ets> foul, base.]</ety>
<def>Inherent baseness or vileness of principle, words, or actions;
shameful wickedness; depravity.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

